{"_id":"0n7gQplLiQZCHJAk","name":"Darkness","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.E7zlNpW4bIfWye7K"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/plain-square_invert.svg","description":"<h1>Darkness</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 1</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> 20 radius or more</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> 1 turn or more</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 action or more</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> N/A</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 258</p><br><p>The cleric extinguishes the light of the sun, demonstrating the great power of his deity. From a distance, the darkness appears to be a space of deepest night; no light will penetrate it. Creatures within are blinded.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Darkness]{Darkness}</p>","results":[{"_id":"iGOZqF9fYWthMH0s","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":11,"range":[-99,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"keqrAdcYYI8iH1iF","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The space immediately surrounding the cleric, to a radius of 20, goes completely dark, as if all light had been extinguished. The darkness remains fixed to its location (it does not follow the cleric) and lasts for 1 turn.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[12,13],"drawn":false},{"_id":"WRyYoIdeCWcCOsBP","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric can designate a point within 20 and create a 20-radius sphere of darkness that remains fixed at that point for a duration of 1 turn.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[14,17],"drawn":false},{"_id":"9Crr0y07eNXEIpLW","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric can designate a point within 100 and create a 20-radius sphere of darkness that remains fixed at that point for a duration of 1 turn.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[18,19],"drawn":false},{"_id":"fBmQuotGiRievxyW","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric can designate a point within 100 and create a 20-radius sphere of darkness centered at that point. The darkness remains for a duration of 1 turn. By concentrating on future rounds, the cleric can move the sphere of darkness up to 40 per round, beyond the original 100 range if he so chooses.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[20,23],"drawn":false},{"_id":"6ZhxvXEmXYqXmvOG","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric can designate a point within 200 and create a sphere of darkness of up to 40 radius centered at that point. The darkness remains for a duration of 2 turns. By concentrating on future rounds, the cleric can move the sphere of darkness up to 80 per round, beyond the original 100 range if he so chooses.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[24,27],"drawn":false},{"_id":"jppDQHo1Wv9Kc1WH","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric can extinguish sources of light. He designates a point within 200, and a sphere of darkness up to 40 in radius appears at that point. The cleric can move this sphere at a speed of 80 per round. No concentration is required. The sphere lasts for 1 hour. In addition, all terrestrial sources of light within the sphere of darkness are extinguished. Torches go out, lanterns sputter and die, glowworms fade, and so on.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[28,29],"drawn":false},{"_id":"zsOduXKd9YVOTVm2","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"With a sweep of his arm, the cleric can cast an enormous space into darkness. The cleric can choose one of three effects: a cone extending 400 to a final width of 100; a sphere up to 60 radius centered at any point within 300; or a wide line, up to 1,000 long and 10 wide. Within the area of effect, total darkness reigns; no light source can penetrate.<br /><br /> In addition, all terrestrial sources of light within the sphere the darkness are extinguished. Torches go out, lanterns sputter and die, glowworms fade, and so on. However, the cleric can see through the darkness. The dark space can be moved up to 100 per round without concentration. It lasts for up to 1 day or until dismissed.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[30,31],"drawn":false},{"_id":"1Wfo4r3FFtF5yagp","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric can blot out the sun, the moon, the stars, or other sources of light. This extraordinary display of divine power requires great concentration. If this result is achieved, the cleric may continue to concentrate. All light sources that illuminate a space 500 in all directions begin to fade. For every round the cleric concentrates, light sources fade by [[/roll 1d20]]%. Torches still burn, but their flames seem to emit less light each round. The judge rolls each round the cleric continues to concentrate. When the total breaks 100%, all light sources have been completely extinguished, and the countryside around the cleric is completely darkened (at least to the eyes of all within 500  the sun still seems to shine in other kingdoms). <br /><br />Once all light sources are extinguished, the radius of the effect begins to expand by another [[/roll 1d20]] per round of concentration. The maximum range is the clerics CL x 1,000. The effect continues as long as the cleric concentrates. When concentration is broken, the light reappears at the same rate it was extinguished; e.g., if it took 7 rounds to fade, it takes 7 rounds to reach full strength again.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":68,"range":[32,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"152wClBTTbJTSFXq","name":"Wood Wyrding","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.9558LVgW0FKAOYLp"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/branch-arrow.svg","description":"<h1>Wood Wyrding</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 2</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> 30 + 5 per CL</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> Varies</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 round</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> None</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 284</p><br><p>The cleric destroys the functionality of wooden objects, rendering them useless or causing them to attack their owners.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Wood Wyrding]{Wood Wyrding}</p>","results":[{"_id":"43wzX8O3E4CIANCs","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":13,"range":[-99,13],"drawn":false},{"_id":"hxKZ2OPqFGZk5Zaz","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric causes a wooden object 5 square or smaller to bend and warp, destroying its functionality. Shutters spring open, arrows and spears become bent and useless, affected melee weapons impart a -4 penalty to attack rolls, chest lids pop open, etc.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[14,15],"drawn":false},{"_id":"yAh3rMGN6GI8IBJu","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric causes a wooden object 10 square or smaller to bend and warp, destroying its functionality. Doors become jammed in their frames, small boats spring leaks, wagon wheels warp, etc. The cleric can affect multiple, smaller, wooden objects as long as they do not exceed the affected size in total.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[16,19],"drawn":false},{"_id":"rNSBiwTpT3XMnSh7","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric causes a wooden object 20 square or smaller to bend and warp, destroying its functionality. Bridges break, roofs collapse, walls buckle, sailing ships spring leaks, etc. The cleric can affect multiple, smaller, wooden objects as long as they do not exceed the affected size in total.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[20,21],"drawn":false},{"_id":"OalTeLyv1DIxbCNq","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric causes a number of small wooden objects equal to his level to suddenly sprout long, sharp thorns that inflict [[/roll 1d6]]+CL damage to any creature carrying, wearing, or otherwise touching the affected objects. Carried objects are automatically dropped. The affected objects cannot be larger than a spear or shield. Magical wooden objects are unaffected.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[22,25],"drawn":false},{"_id":"5NazfrNaPm3xTUni","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric changes one item per CL (of spear size or smaller) into a serpent that attacks other creatures as commanded by the cleric. Magical wooden objects are unaffected. Each serpent has the following stats: Init +1; Atk bite +2 melee (dmg [[/roll 1d3]]+CL), AC 12, HD [[/roll 1d8]]+CL; MV 30; SV Fort +3, Ref +4, Will +2, AL N. In addition, there is a cumulative 5% per CL that the serpents are venomous (DC 12 Fort or [[/roll 1d3]] Stamina).","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[26,29],"drawn":false},{"_id":"A6Sq0DESM3dIHCla","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric changes one item per CL (of spear size or smaller) into an even larger serpent that attacks other creatures as commanded by the cleric. Magical wooden objects are unaffected. Each serpent has the following stats: Init +3; Atk bite +4 melee (dmg [[/roll 1d6]]+CL), AC 14, HD [[/roll 2d8]]+CL; MV 30; SV Fort +4, Ref +6, Will +2, AL N. In addition, there is a cumulative 10% per CL that the serpents are venomous (DC 14 Fort or death).","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[30,31],"drawn":false},{"_id":"c4YSQG2UJktIFshV","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric has terrifying command over wooden objects. He may warp objects the size of tall trees, destroying wooden palisades, collapsing massive bridges, causing catapults and siege towers to fail spectacularly, etc. Moreover, using the same warped wood, he can transform any sufficiently shaped segment of the destroyed object (such as a fallen tree, log, or beam) into a titanic serpent with the stats of a giant boa constrictor (see Appendix P) that obeys his commands.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[32,33],"drawn":false},{"_id":"NeEFlUqO9rS7t6YX","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"With a startling invocation, the cleric invokes the power of his deity to destroy all wooden objects near him. To a range of 100 per CL, he causes all wood to instantaneously rot, leaving nothing but spongy powder behind. Even magical wood may be affected, with a chance of 5% per CL. <br /><br />This spell effectively disarms armed troops wielding spears, bows and arrows, or other wooden weapons; destroys wood-frame homes, possibly crushing those within; causes entire wooden palisades to vanish; sinks fleets of ships; and causes other spectacular effects.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":66,"range":[34,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"1cfL6flvt8lSN7xa","name":"Remove Curse","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.hIwErP0RHJGvPZRs"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/holy-water.svg","description":"<h1>Remove Curse</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 3</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> Touch</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> Instantaneous</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 round</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> See below</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 289</p><br><p>The cleric calls upon divine power to banish the baleful effects of a curse on a person or object. As referenced in the spell descriptions below, a minor curse is one that causes a loss of 2 or less ability score points; a moderate curse is one that impacts 3-4 ability score points or has a limiting effect of some kind (penalty to rolls, reduced speed, etc.); and a major curse is one that impacts 5+ ability score points or has a debilitating effect (blindness, deafness, immobility, etc.). When a save is called for, the affected individual or object either makes a second saving throw against the curse (save and DC are the same as the original curse), or, if no save was allowed against the original curse, the creature or object may make either a Fort or Will save (player&rsquo;s discretion) against a DC of 10 + the HD of creature that bestowed the curse. If the save is successful, the cursed creature or object is no longer affected by the curse. If the save fails, the curse remains in effect and 24 hours must pass before the cleric can again attempt to remove the curse.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Remove Curse]{Remove Curse}</p>","results":[{"_id":"nmJuP8KTWEpsq2qW","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":15,"range":[-99,15],"drawn":false},{"_id":"59VlPqDqUD1nEWDj","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A single cursed individual or object is allowed to make a new saving throw to escape the effects of a minor curse.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[16,17],"drawn":false},{"_id":"itBOldK2hQrNBdEG","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A number of cursed individuals or objects equal to the clerics CL are allowed to make a saving throw to escape the effects of a minor curse. If only a single cursed creature or object is targeted, they gain a bonus to their saving throw equal to the CL.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[18,21],"drawn":false},{"_id":"m4DxGlNiSABb48r5","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric automatically removes a minor curse from a single individual or allows a saving throw to remove a moderate curse from a single cursed individual or object.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[22,23],"drawn":false},{"_id":"4FwIWbXdctFFOIl6","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric automatically removes a minor curse from a number or individuals or objects equal to his CL or allows a saving throw to remove a moderate curse from a number of cursed individuals or objects equal to his CL. If only a single cursed creature or object is targeted, it gains a bonus to the saving throw equal to the CL.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":3,"range":[24,26],"drawn":false},{"_id":"cxglJ8QHYdqjQt73","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric automatically removes a minor or moderate curse from a single individual or allows a saving throw to remove a major curse for a single cursed individual or object.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":5,"range":[27,31],"drawn":false},{"_id":"v3ZFPyTQXNiyKqnQ","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric automatically removes a minor or moderate curse from a number or individuals or objects equal to his CL or allows saving throw to remove a major curse for a number of cursed individuals or objects equal to his CL. If only a single cursed creature or object is targeted, they gain a bonus to their saving throw equal to the CL.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[32,33],"drawn":false},{"_id":"TmHL4tUCHQpNc93w","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric automatically removes any curse affecting a single creature or object, regardless of the curses potency.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[34,35],"drawn":false},{"_id":"63XCTguEReC0CxcZ","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric automatically removes any curse affecting a number of creatures equal to his CL. In addition, if the creature or creatures that bestowed the curse(s) is currently alive, it automatically becomes the victim of its own curse regardless of its location or distance away from the cleric.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":64,"range":[36,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"4HrmJHl3r1j31Adj","name":"Detect Evil","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.ONtUy27MjxrnG6CQ"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/spyglass.svg","description":"<h1>Detect Evil</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 1</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> 60 radius from cleric or more (see below)</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> 6 turns</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 action</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> Will vs. spell check DC (sometimes)</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 259</p><br><p>The cleric holds up his holy symbol and detects emanations of evil within a ray that extends straight out 5&rsquo; wide and 60&rsquo; (or more) ahead of the symbol. The definition of &ldquo;evil&rdquo; is based on the cleric: generally it encompasses creatures of opposed alignment, those unholy to the cleric&rsquo;s deity, and those with clearly harmful intent. Depending on the strength of the spell, it may detect even more subtle dangers. This spell does not reveal creatures that are otherwise hidden but does inform the cleric that evil intentions radiate from a certain position. This spell may be reversed to detect good, which means creatures of allied alignment, common deity, or similar holy goals.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Detect Evil]{Detect Evil}</p>","results":[{"_id":"aHo0zOLX8a3hfi7p","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":11,"range":[-99,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"YfJMskVCXOyyDCgu","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Creatures of opposed alignment are potentially detected, as well as objects inherently dangerous in nature (such as traps and cursed weapons). Evil creatures receive a Will save vs. spell check DC to remain undetected by this spell.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[12,13],"drawn":false},{"_id":"ylj6Fpsa4lxlRCWK","flags":{},"type":0