{"_id":"EP54iPFxMQNhk0X0","name":"Detect Magic","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.Sl4QKUjrhwiQNv4U"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/magic-swirl.svg","description":"<h1>Detect Magic</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 1</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> 30 or more</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> 2 turns</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 2 actions</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> Will vs. spell check DC (sometimes)</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 260</p><br><p>The cleric knows if there has been an enchantment laid upon a person, place or thing within range. The range is a cone, 30&rsquo; long and 30&rsquo; wide at its end, emanating from the cleric&rsquo;s holy symbol.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Detect Magic]{Detect Magic}</p>","results":[{"_id":"pLfSkkSHso3iachp","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":11,"range":[-99,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"8RvWxJoTaVDrmFXf","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric is aware of magical enchantment on any object or creature within range. This includes weapons or armor worn by a creature, as well as spells. The cleric cannot distinguish which portions of the targets are magical. For example, a creature enchanted by a spell or carrying a magical weapon or item registers simply as magical, so the true extent and nature of the magic is not always evident.<br /><br /> The cleric does not receive any information on the nature of the magical enchantment, only its existence. Intelligent magic creatures and creations that wish to hide their magical nature can do so with a Will save. Objects behind 3 of wood, 1 of solid metal, or 1 of stone are not detected.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[12,13],"drawn":false},{"_id":"BBVJo0xrOXk4x1Xm","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric is aware of magical enchantm