{"_id":"IDiFeOQVKOddbuKs","name":"Second Sight","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.YcY1od3zamrki69V"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/octogonal-eye.svg","description":"<h1>Second Sight</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 1</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> Self</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> 1 round or more</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 turn</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> N/A</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 267</p><br><p>Using sortilege, haruspicy, or some other method appropriate to the cleric, he augurs the future. In doing so, the cleric gains insight about the consequences his actions will bring.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Second Sight]{Second Sight}</p>","results":[{"_id":"PdQJmFLGZCvwfNat","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":11,"range":[-99,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"jUYHBjplKA3GKGxn","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"For one round, the cleric glimpses the future. In doing so, he gains great insight into the most effective manner to complete any action. The cleric receive a +4 bonus to a single roll of his choosing on his next round, whether its an attack roll, damage roll, skill check, or something else.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[12,13],"drawn":false},{"_id":"tWrsOndlBu8jhrGl","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric has a hint of possible outcomes. He must spend the following round concentrating on a choice that must be made in the next 30 minutes. For example, he may be deciding which direction to turn in a dungeon or whether to enter a room. The cleric gets a sense of whether the action will be to his benefit or harm. There is a 75% chance that the sense the cleric receives is accurate.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[14,17],"drawn":false},{"_id":"QI8ucF0R3ikioBml","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric has a hint of possible outcomes. He must spend the following round concentrating on a choice that must be made in the next 30 minutes. For example, he may be deciding which direction to turn in a dungeon or whether to enter a room. The cleric gets a sense of whether the action will be to his benefit or harm. There is an 80% chance that the sense the cleric receives is accurate.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[18,19],"drawn":false},{"_id":"ECQu1JbU4R4mL4EB","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric has a hint of possible outcomes. He must spend the following round concentrating on a choice that must be made in the next 30 minutes. For example, he may be deciding which direction to turn in a dungeon or whether to enter a room. The cleric gets a sense of whether the action will be to his benefit or harm. There is an 85% chance that the sense the cleric receives is accurate.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[20,23],"drawn":false},{"_id":"pTiY1auSXRpERAlg","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"For the next hour, the cleric receives an ongoing sense of possible outcomes. At every significant decision or juncture, he receives a premonition regarding the decision he must make  a sense of foreboding or certitude depending on whether the action bodes well for him (or not). For any given action, there is an 85% chance that the sense is accurate. By concentrating, the cleric can receive a sense of whether a future action (one to be taken within in the next hour) will be a bane or boon.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[24,27],"drawn":false},{"_id":"Jl7jHnuYpgIQ4hQX","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"For the next hour, the cleric receives an ongoing sense of possible outcomes. At every significant decision or juncture, he receives a premonition regarding the decision he must make  a sense of foreboding or certitude depending on whether the action bodes well for him (or not). For any given action, there is a 90% chance that the sense is accurate. By concentrating, the cleric can receive a sense of whether a future action (one to be taken within in the next hour) will be a bane or boon.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[28,29],"drawn":false},{"_id":"PwRpL2nBylwRaOzl","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"For the next day, the cleric receives an ongoing sense of possible outcomes. At every significant decision or juncture, he receives a premonition regarding the decision he must make  a sense of foreboding or certitude depending on whether the action bodes well for him (or not). For any given action, there is a 95% chance that the sense is accurate. <br /><br />By concentrating, the cleric can receive a sense of whether a future action (one to be taken within in the next day) will be a bane or boon. For example, a cleric could divine the results of a great battle to be fought on the morrow and gain a sense that although he will emerge unharmed from the battle, it will be harmful to his church.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[30,31],"drawn":false},{"_id":"BcG0voRXQNJxrS8d","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric has read the tablets of time. For the next month, he receives an ongoing sense of possible outcomes. At every significant decision or juncture, he receives a premonition regarding the decision he must make  a sense of foreboding or certitude depending on whether the action bodes well for him (or not). For any given action, there is a 99% chance that the sense is accurate. <br /><br />By concentrating, the cleric can receive a sense of whether a future action (one to be taken within in the next day) will be a bane or boon. For example, a cleric could divine the results of a great battle to be fought on the morrow and gain a sense that although he will emerge unharmed from the battle, it will be harmful to his church. In addition, the cleric receive a +1 bonus to all rolls while the second sight is active, reflecting his general insight into the consequences of all actions.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":68,"range":[32,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"ImkSJtrBHFH3jRng","name":"Bolt from the Blue","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.cF8K9n4Uy27zZVgL"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/lightning-storm.svg","description":"<h1>Bolt from the Blue</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 3</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> 100</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> 1 round</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 action</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> See below</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 287</p><br><p>The cleric calls down divine vengeance upon those who stand in the way of his deity&rsquo;s agenda, causing physical and mental anguish, loss of ability scores, and other debilitating results.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Bolt from the Blue]{Bolt from the Blue}</p>","results":[{"_id":"MaM8uX6rszcfp9XJ","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":15,"range":[-99,15],"drawn":false},{"_id":"YFQc4DHXhAlNUGNe","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A single bolt streaks down to strike one target of the clerics choice within range. The bolt does [[/roll 1d6]] points of damage and the victim must make a successful Fort save or temporarily lose a single point from one of its abilities (determined by the judge or at random).","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[16,17],"drawn":false},{"_id":"3CWeRz9qMvqsJE2V","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A single bolt streaks down to strike one target of the clerics choice within the spells range. The bolt does [[/roll 1d8]] points of damage and the target must make a successful Fort save the following round in order to perform any action.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[18,21],"drawn":false},{"_id":"NQgdKXwYnqnznBpe","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric can unleash a number of bolts equal to his CL, which must be aimed at a single target within the spells range. Each bolt does [[/roll 1d10]] points of damage and requires the victim to make a successful Fort save. Failure indicates the target is paralyzed for [[/roll 1d4]] rounds and temporarily loses a single point from one of its ability scores (determined by the judge or at random). Paralysis and ability score loss from multiple failed saves do stack.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[22,23],"drawn":false},{"_id":"wpJQaJZZ1RtIu9my","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric can unleash a number of bolts equal to his CL, which can be aimed at multiple targets within the spells range. These bolts cause [[/roll 1d12]] damage, and cause each target to temporarily lose [[/roll 1d2+1]] points from a single ability score (determined by the judge or at random). In addition, each target must make a Will save or go insane for [[/roll 1d4]] rounds.<br /><br /> The judge should check each round to determine the actions of the afflicted while the insanity lasts. Each round there is a 50% chance they do nothing other than tear at their hair, babble incoherently, and froth at the mouth; a 25% chance they attack a nearby creature at random; and a 25% chance they perform a normal action.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":3,"range":[24,26],"drawn":false},{"_id":"dVR8hzlIDTG8ETEA","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric can unleash a number of bolts equal to twice his CL, which can be aimed at multiple targets within the spells range. These bolts cause [[/roll 1d14]] damage and cause each target to temporarily lose [[/roll 1d3]] points from a single ability score (determined by the judge or at random). In addition, each target must make a Fort save or be crippled for [[/roll 1d4]] rounds. During this time, their movement rate is reduced to 5 and they suffer a -4 penalty to all attacks, damage, saving throws, and spell checks.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":5,"range":[27,31],"drawn":false},{"_id":"uqNcnR4vdOE2KR7n","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric can unleash a number of bolts equal to twice his CL, which can be aimed at multiple targets within the spells range. These bolts cause [[/roll 1d16]] damage and cause each target to temporarily lose [[/roll 1d4]] points from a single ability score (determined by the judge or at random). In addition, each target must make a Will save or be cursed (as the cleric spell). Another spell check is made to determine the potency of the curse using all the same modifiers as the clerics initial spell check for bolt from the blue, and the final result is compared to the curse spell table.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[32,33],"drawn":false},{"_id":"w4RwPBFIp4JsbqRj","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric can unleash a number of bolts equal to twice his CL, which can be aimed at multiple targets within the spells range. These bolts cause [[/roll 1d20]] damage and cause each target to temporarily lose [[/roll 1d5+1]] points from a single ability score (determined by the judge or at random). In addition, each target must make a Will save or permanently lose one point from that ability.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[34,35],"drawn":false},{"_id":"cZaTajw7EdnByw83","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric can unleash a number of bolts equal to twice his CL, which can be aimed at multiple targets within the spells range. These bolts cause [[/roll 1d30]] damage and cause each target to permanently lose [[/roll 1d3]] points from a single ability score (determined by the judge or at random). In addition, each target is branded with a symbol of the deitys displeasure. Such marked individuals are treated as enemies of the clerics faith and attacked on sight. <br /><br />In addition, all spell checks against those targets by clerics of the offended deity enjoy a +10 bonus. Only miraculous magics by another powerful cleric or a sincere quest on behalf of the offended deitys church can remove this mark once it has been bestowed on a subject.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":64,"range":[36,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"K4MAk7nEdSQDuGCr","name":"Holy Sanctuary","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.Af9FFPnrxtfntCAC"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/laurels.svg","description":"<h1>Holy Sanctuary</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 1</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> Self or more</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> 1 round or more</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 action</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> Will save vs. spell check</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 263</p><br><p>The cleric invokes a place of sanctuary where he and his allies are safe from harm.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Holy Sanctuary]{Holy Sanctuary}</p>","results":[{"_id":"07FuLX3pffuopY21","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":11,"range":[-99,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"gnCvxqDiITkEzQTi","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Enemies find it difficult to focus on attacking the cleric. They are distracted, and the cleric is more easily able to dodge their attacks. All attacks against the cleric for the next round suffer a -2 penalty.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[12,13],"drawn":false},{"_id":"B04sCSYYiih9nbZZ","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Enemies are compelled to focus their attacks against other targets. As long as an attacker can reasonably attack some other target instead of the cleric, it must choose to do so. In order to resist this compulsion and attack the cleric, an enemy must make a Will save vs. spell check DC. If the cleric is the only reasonable target, the creature need not make a save to attack the cleric. This effect lasts for 1 turn. It is immediately dispelled if the cleric attacks or takes aggressive action in any way.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[14,17],"drawn":false},{"_id":"DIB4j1S5KKHXWWd4","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Enemies are compelled to focus their attacks against other targets. As long as an attacker can reasonably attack some other target instead of the cleric, it must choose to do so. In order to resist this compulsion and attack the cleric, an enemy must make a Will save vs. spell check DC. This Will save is required even if the cleric is the only reasonable target. This effect lasts for 1 turn. It is immediately dispelled if the cleric attacks or takes aggressive action in any way.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[18,19],"drawn":false},{"_id":"qGkf9JO4Q2Lmo2tj","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Enemies are compelled to focus their attacks against other targets. As long as an attacker can reasonably attack some other target instead of the cleric, it must choose to do so. Creatures of 3 HD or less cannot attack the cleric in any manner.<br /><br /> Creatures of 4 HD or more may attempt a Will save to resist the compulsion and attack the cleric. This Will save is required even if the cleric is the only reasonable target. This effect lasts for 1 turn. It is immediately dispelled if the cleric attacks or takes aggressive action in any way.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[20,23],"drawn":false},{"_id":"wW7xgnZdIYVPdaX4","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric can create a holy sanctuary that includes himself and up to two allies within 5. The other protected allies must remain within 5 or the effect ends. Enemies are compelled to focus their attacks against other targets. <br /><br />As long as an attacker can reasonably attack some other target instead of the cleric and his protected allies, it must choose to do so. Creatures of 3 HD or less cannot attack in any manner; creatures of 4 HD or more may attempt a Will save to resist the compulsion. This effect lasts for 1 turn. It is immediately dispelled if the cleric or any of his protected allies attack or take aggressive action in any way.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[24,27],"drawn":false},{"_id":"0ulNGBElAEdEQfOx","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric may designate a place as a holy sanctuary. This must be a single building or self-contained location up to 5,000 square feet in area; e.g., a church, forest grove, or cave. This effect lasts for [[/roll 1d7]] days. Creatures within this place share the benefits of a holy sanctuary as follows, provided they are in the service of the clerics deity: enemies of less than 6 HD cannot attack unless they use magical weapons, and enemies of 7+ HD or those using magical weapons must make a Will save vs. spell check DC to attack. <br /><br />The effect on any one individual is dispelled if that creature makes an aggressive action. Note that enemies can still enter the place and converse with its residents; they simply cannot attack or make other aggressive actions.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[28,29],"drawn":false},{"_id":"tzYI9UbfoeC1wE9F","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric may designate a place as a holy sanctuary. This must be a single building or self-contained location up to 5,000 square feet in area; e.g., a church, forest grove, or cave. This effect lasts for [[/roll 1d7+3]] weeks. Creatures within this place share the benefits of a holy sanctuary as follows, provided they are in the service of the clerics deity: enemies of less than 6 HD cannot attack unless they use magical weapons, and enemies of 7+ HD or those using magical weapons must make a Will save vs. spell check DC to attack. <br /><br />The effect on any one individual is dispelled if that creature makes an aggressive action. Note that enemies can still enter the place and converse with its residents; they simply cannot attack or make other aggressive actions.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[30,31],"drawn":false},{"_id":"AuKWmvjs8QXdqtYO","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric may designate a place as a holy sanctuary. This must be a single building or self-contained location up to 10,000 square feet in area; e.g., a church, forest grove, or cave. The place designated as a holy sanctuary becomes sanctified forever, as long as the clerics deity retains respect for the clerics work and actions. Creatures within this place share the benefits of a holy sanctuary as follows, provided they are in the service of the clerics deity: enemies of less than 6 HD cannot attack unless they use magical weapons, and enemies of 7+ HD or those using magical weapons must make a Will save vs. spell check DC to attack. <br /><br />The effect on any one individual is dispelled if that creature makes an aggressive action. Note that enemies can still enter the place and converse with its residents; they simply cannot attack or make other aggressive actions.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":68,"range":[32,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"L7m8ZoLNx9evT0Wl","name":"Resist Cold or Heat","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.7f847YPuJoiN6g74"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/burning-passion.svg","description":"<h1>Resist Cold or Heat</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 1</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> Self or more</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> 1 round or more</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 action</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> N/A</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 266</p><br><p>The cleric repels the chilling effects of cold or heat, protecting himself and others. He can withstand such conditions without discomfort. When casting the spell, the cleric chooses which effect to resist (heat or cold). It is possible to cast the spell twice and create a resistance to both effects.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Resist Cold or Heat]{Resist Cold or Heat}</p>","results":[{"_id":"ZFuNnWdWXM4Zin0Z","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":11,"range":[-99,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"U6JyDy1JdYKmJlzf","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric counteracts the harmful effects of cold or heat upon his body. He can ignore up to 5 points of cold or heat/fire damage in the next round. If more than 5 points is sustained, subtract 5 from the total dice result to determine the final damage suffered.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[12,13],"drawn":false},{"_id":"rh0LJGwmi9DUHJEJ","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric counteracts the harmful effects of cold or heat upon his body. He can ignore up to 5 points of cold or heat/fire damage for a number of rounds equal to [[/roll 1d6]]+CL. If more than 5 points is sustained in a given round, subtract 5 from the total dice result to determine the final damage suffered.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[14,17],"drawn":false},{"_id":"CkCImX3E0O4HNVZL","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric counteracts the harmful effects of cold or heat upon his body. He can ignore up to 10 points of cold or heat/fire damage for a number of rounds equal to [[/roll 1d8]]+CL. If more than 10 points is sustained in a given round, subtract 10 from the total dice result to determine the final damage suffered.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[18,19],"drawn":false},{"_id":"qLHC6S06ff698ygM","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric counteracts the harmful effects of cold or heat upon his body. He can ignore up to 10 points of cold or heat/fire damage for a number of rounds equal to [[/roll 1d8]]+CL. If more than 10 points is sustained in a given round, subtract 10 from the total dice result to determine the final damage suffered. In addition, the cleric also receives a +4 bonus to all saving throws to resist cold- or heat-based effects.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[20,23],"drawn":false},{"_id":"hfg5edenwV9ybwBI","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric can protect others as well as himself. The cleric produces a sphere of resistance that emanates 10 from his location. Everyone within this sphere can resist up to 10 points of cold or heat damage per round and receive a +2 bonus to all saving throws against cold- or heat-based effects. The cleric must concentrate to maintain the sphere, which can remain functioning for up to 1 turn.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[24,27],"drawn":false},{"_id":"BSqkD6tdq0xfwvFY","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric can protect others as well as himself. The cleric produces a sphere of resistance that emanates 20 from his location. Everyone within this sphere can resist up to 20 points of cold or heat damage per round and receive a +4 bonus to all saving throws against cold- or heat-based effects. The cleric must concentrate to maintain the sphere, which can remain functioning for up to 1 turn.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[28,29],"drawn":false},{"_id":"5KwscgTM3rFafJui","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric can protect others as well as himself. The cleric produces a sphere of resistance that emanates 20 from his location. Everyone within this sphere can resist up to 20 points of cold or heat damage per round and receive a +4 bonus to all saving throws against cold- or heat-based effects. <br /><br />The sphere continues to function, without concentration, for a number of rounds equal to [[/roll 1d10]]+CL. Each time it is about to expire, the cleric can concentrate for one round to extend the effect another [[/roll 1d10]]+CL rounds, to a maximum duration of one hour.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[30,31],"drawn":false},{"_id":"lA1T1Hwhgz5pxnPO","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric can protect others as well as himself. The cleric produces a sphere of resistance that emanates 50 from his location. Everyone within this sphere can resist up to 30 points of cold or heat damage per round and receive a +6 bonus to all saving throws against cold- or heat-based effects. <br /><br />The sphere continues to function, without concentration, for a number of turns equal to [[/roll 1d6]]+CL. Each time it is about to expire, the cleric can concentrate for one round to extend the effect another [[/roll 1d6]]+CL turns, to a maximum duration of one day.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":68,"range":[32,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"MtA4jqwKW6Mfd6by","name":"Exorcise","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.Ns7q7lvfgBGSi0vQ"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/crucifix.svg","description":"<h1>Exorcise</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 3</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> 1 mile per CL (but see below)</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> Instantaneous</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 hour</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> See below</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 288</p><br><p>The cleric calls upon divine forces to tear asunder the bonds linking mortals and their supernatural patrons, at the risk of drawing unwanted attention to himself. This spell requires much from the cleric and can only be performed once every seven days after a period of fasting, prayer, and mental preparation. Typically, an item belonging to the target, or a piece of the target&rsquo;s physical body (hair, blood, fingernail,</p>\n<p>etc.) is required to cast this spell. Attempting the spell without such an item imposes a -4 penalty to the spell check. Additionally, casting the spell without a physical link to the target reduces the range of the spell to 100&rsquo; per CL.</p>\n<p>When cast, the cleric makes a spell check as normal. If his spell check exceeds the spell check made when the original patron bond was cast, the bond is broken and the subject of the bond loses all benefits of that bond immediately. This can include losing patron spells he has previously learned. The subject cannot attempt to reform the patron bond until one month has past or some powerful magic has offset the exorcism.</p>\n<p>In addition, the subject may suffer side effects from the breaking of the bond (see below).</p>\n<p>If the cleric&rsquo;s spell check is insufficient to break the patron bond, it is likely that the powers involved attempt to punish the cleric for his meddling. The cleric must make a Luck check to avoid drawing attention to himself and facing the wrath of the supernatural agents involved. If the Luck check fails, the cleric can expect to face the patron&rsquo;s minions, or at higher levels, the patron itself!</p>\n<p>While the text of this spell refers to a patron bond, the spell could be used in a similar manner to break other, similar supernatural bonds, where they are encountered.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Exorcise]{Exorcise}</p>","results":[{"_id":"1NI5gRk4ap3rKApt","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure. The cleric must make a DC 5 Luck check to avoid attracting the patrons notice. If failed, the subject is alerted that someone is attempting to sever his patron bond.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":15,"range":[-99,15],"drawn":false},{"_id":"6dkrcqq7jWoAQd0n","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric exorcises a patron bond whose original spell check was less than the clerics spell check roll. The subject of the bond is dazed for [[/roll 1d6]] rounds as the bond breaks, suffering a -2 penalty to all rolls during that time. If the clerics spell check was insufficient to break the bond, he must make a DC 10 Luck check to avoid the patrons notice. If failed, a minor agent of the patron (judges choice) seeks out the cleric with the intent to harm him. It arrives in [[/roll 1d5]] days after the failed casting.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[16,17],"drawn":false},{"_id":"wvau7uWB6ZnVlWtn","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric exorcises a patron bond whose original spell check was less than the clerics spell check roll. The subject of the bond is paralyzed for [[/roll 1d6]] rounds as the bond breaks. If the clerics spell check was insufficient to break the bond, he must make a DC 12 Luck check to avoid the patrons notice. If failed, a minor agent of the patron (judges choice) seeks out the cleric with the intent to harm him. It arrives in [[/roll 1d4]] days after the failed casting.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[18,21],"drawn":false},{"_id":"qulnC9tgqa9X1DM5","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric exorcises a patron bond whose original spell check was less than the clerics spell check roll. The subject of the bond takes  [[/roll 1d6]]+CL in damage as the bond severs. If the clerics spell check was insufficient to break the bond, he must make a DC 14 Luck check to avoid the patrons notice. If failed, a moderately powerful agent of the patron (judges choice) seeks out the cleric with the intent to harm him. It arrives in [[/roll 1d3]] days after the failed casting.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[22,23],"drawn":false},{"_id":"9o5d4FUeFZtENlWN","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric exorcises a patron bond whose original spell check was less than the clerics spell check roll. The subject of the bond takes  [[/roll 1d8]]+CL in damage and 1 point of temporary ability damage (chosen at random) as the bond severs.<br /><br /> If the clerics spell check was insufficient to break the bond, he must make a DC 16 Luck check to avoid the patrons notice. If failed, a moderately powerful agent of the patron (judges choice) seeks out the cleric with the intent to harm him. It arrives in [[/roll 1d2]] days after the failed casting.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":3,"range":[24,26],"drawn":false},{"_id":"I7O3K6POVgBERwey","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric exorcises a patron bond whose original spell check was less than the clerics spell check roll. As the bond severs, the subject of the bond takes [[/roll 1d10]]+CL in damage, 1 point of temporary ability damage (chosen at random), and loses the ability to cast one random spell for the day if a spellcaster.<br /><br /> If the clerics spell check was insufficient to break the bond, he must make a DC 18 Luck check to avoid the patrons notice. If failed, a moderately powerful agent of the patron (judges choice) seeks out the cleric with the intent to harm him. It arrives in [[/roll 1d2]] days after the failed casting.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":5,"range":[27,31],"drawn":false},{"_id":"Pb7Rv562nknovRfT","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric exorcises a patron bond whose original spell check was less than the clerics spell check roll. As the bond severs, the subject of the bond takes [[/roll 2d6]]+CL in damage, 2 points of temporary ability damage (chosen at random), and must make a Will save or be struck senseless for [[/roll 1d6]] hours.<br /><br /> If the clerics spell check was insufficient to break the bond, he must make a DC 20 Luck check to avoid the patrons notice. If failed, a powerful agent of the patron (judges choice) seeks out the cleric with the intent to harm him. It arrives the day the casting failed. If the Luck check is successful, the cleric still suffers cosmic backlash and becomes the subject of a minor curse of the judges choosing.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[32,33],"drawn":false},{"_id":"qQb1h9wFQor2KFS9","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric exorcises a patron bond whose original spell check was less than the clerics spell check roll. As the bond severs, the subject of the bond takes [[/roll 3d6]]+CL in damage, 3 points of temporary ability damage (chosen at random), and must make a Will save or lose all spells for 24 hours if a spellcaster.<br /><br /> If the clerics spell check was insufficient to break the bond, he must make a DC 22 Luck check to avoid the patrons notice. If failed, an extremely powerful agent of the patron (judges choice) seeks out the cleric with the intent to harm him. It arrives within [[/roll 1d12]] hours of the failed casting. If the Luck check is successful, the cleric still suffers cosmic backlash and becomes the subject of a minor curse of the judges choosing.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[34,35],"drawn":false},{"_id":"CuZeKzfhu5oUOfLn","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric exorcises a patron bond whose original spell check was less than the clerics spell check roll. As the bond severs, the subject must make a DC 22 Fort save. If successful, he suffers [[/roll 3d8]]+CL damage, 4 points of temporary ability damage (chosen at random) and loses 1 permanent ability point. If the save is failed, he undergoes a horrific physical transformation, his body wracked by supernatural forces gone awry.<br /><br /> The exact details of the transformation are left to the judge, but could include becoming a horrific monster, turned into mobile slime, transmutation into sentient, immobile stone, etc. If the clerics spell check was insufficient to break the bond, he automatically attracts the attention of the subjects patron who immediately appears at the clerics location with the intent of destroying him.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":64,"range":[36,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"PACw53KTbCzkmhai","name":"Snake Charm","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"RollTable.lgNq6lzdOIixtS6z"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/snake-jar.svg","description":"<h1>Snake Charm</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 2</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> 30 or more</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> Varies</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 round</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> Will vs. spell check DC (sometimes)</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 280</p><br><p>The cleric can control snakes within his presence or potentially summon snakes to do his bidding. The snakes will threaten, guard, attack, or otherwise behave as commanded.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Snake Charm]{Snake Charm}</p>","results":[{"_id":"fd4osClrczRTQuRp","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":13,"range":[-99,13],"drawn":false},{"_id":"fBHF35HYzy8hbMAk","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Nearby snakes acknowledge the cleric as their friend and ally. The range is 30’. Mundane snakes up to 2 HD are affected automatically. Mundane snakes of 3 HD or more, as well as supernatural snake-like creatures up to 4 HD (such as  naga, medusae, snake-men, and so on) receive a Will save to resist. <br /><br />Snakelike creatures of 5 HD or more are not affected. Affected creatures will not attack the cleric under any circumstances. They do not actively assist the cleric, but will not impede his passing. When the cleric passes more than 30’ from any affected creature, it returns to its former attitude regarding him.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[14,15],"drawn":false},{"_id":"7VDem7N99cj9uqP7","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Nearby snakes submit to the cleric as their master. They obey the cleric’s bidding and fight on his behalf. The range is 100’. The effect takes hold automatically on mundane snakes up to 3 HD. Large