a duration of [[/roll 1d4]]+CL weeks, the objects retain their natural shape until they touch an enemy. Once they touch an enemy, they remain in spider or snake form for [[/roll 3d6]]+CL rounds.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[32,33],"drawn":false},{"_id":"LAu8ooTiLG8TPO1e","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric can transform up to 100 sling stones into poisonous spiders, up to 40 arrows into asps or adders, or up to four staves into cobras or vipers. For a duration of [[/roll 1d8]]+CL weeks, the objects retain their natural shape until they touch an enemy. Once they touch an enemy, they remain in spider or snake form for [[/roll 3d6]]+CL rounds. <br /><br />Alternately, the cleric can transform a single object permanently. Specify a single sling stone, arrow, or staff. It is permanently subject to transformation, as noted above. When it changes form into a spider or serpent, it stays in that form for the normal duration of [[/roll 3d6]]+CL rounds, then reverts to its natural state until triggered again. If the “object” is killed while in serpent or spider form, it remains in its dead state and its magical properties are lost.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[34,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"ZwYg44Ql89sOEMLt","name":"Banish","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendiums.dcc-spell-tables.mkLCDGrBIAW5A7Ek"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/exit-door.svg","description":"<h1>Banish</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 2</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> 30 or more</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> Varies</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 round</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> Will vs. spell check DC</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 269</p><br><p>The cleric banishes a creature from his presence and potentially forces it back from whence it came. This spell is usually employed to force a supernatural creature back to its native plane, though it can also be used to send mundane creatures back to their lairs.</p>\n<p>The cleric specifies a single target. This can be a creature within line of sight or a creature that is not present, provided the cleric possesses a physical memento (lock of hair, fingernail, favored weapon, drop of blood, etc.). The cleric then casts the spell, and the target is affected as described below.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Banish]{Banish}</p>","results":[{"_id":"h8ZwHG3KpgesWL4L","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[-99,13],"drawn":false},{"_id":"uNg4UPGa4EPZY8Ca","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"For the next turn, the target must make a Will save to approach within 30 of the cleric. If failed, it cannot approach any closer than 30 nor can it hurl missile weapons, speak in the clerics direction, or otherwise take action against him. If forced within 30, the target takes [[/roll 1d4]]+CL divine damage each round, although this damage cannot kill the creature.<br /><br /> If reduced to 0 hit points, the target collapses, unconscious, and heals normally when removed from the clerics presence. If the spell is cast while the target is already wi