,"resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[36,37],"drawn":false},{"_id":"CBvpVACAEyfebxXh","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric wreaks destruction upon an area 3 miles in radius, centered at any point he can see, even beyond this plane. Scrying devices may allow him to cast this spell over great distances. Massive tremors topple entire fortresses; dams collapse; villages, farmlands, animals, and people are engulfed in chasms; roaring flames erupt from lava spouts; and other titanic examples of devastation occur. The judge may allow those in the area of effect a saving throw to avoid death, but the force of the quake and the damage caused by it is likely fatal to all. Even flying creatures are caught in the updrafts and stormy winds created by the event. The landscape remains permanently altered in the aftermath.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":62,"range":[38,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"gxxozR24TyRoeYKw","name":"Food of the Gods","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.TgcYYijujZz9bONt"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/cornucopia.svg","description":"<h1>Food of the Gods</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 1</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> 30</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> 24 hours (see below)</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 turn</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> N/A</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 262</p><br><p>The cleric calls upon the power of his deity to feed the masses. This spell either makes inedible food edible or magically creates viands when no other food and drink is available. Magically-created food is a spongy, grey, and bland-tasting substance that spoils after 24 hours. Magically-created water is clean rainwater that remains drinkable for as long as it is properly stored.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Food of the Gods]{Food of the Gods}</p>","results":[{"_id":"wSQtmUX3rIeCMKq3","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":11,"range":[-99,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"J1tZBoGdPJYCTM0V","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric can purify enough pre-existing spoiled food and tainted water to feed up to [[/roll 1d6]]+CL people. This spell merely makes normally inedible food edible and has no effect on poison. This result does not create new food or water from thin air.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[12,13],"drawn":false},{"_id":"nhn2IXE5uqH7CPRa","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric creates food and water from thin air, creating enough to feed 5+CL people.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[14,17],"drawn":false},{"_id":"SMwyy5hQYt3NPHzd","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric creates food and water from thin air, creating enough to feed 10+CL people.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[18,19],"drawn":false},{"_id":"HER0DzwpIXEH7AXT","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric creates food and water from thin air, creating enough to feed 15+CL people.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[20,23],"drawn":false},{"_id":"AEWNuDTs171R3gpC","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric creates food and water from thin air, creating enough to feed 20+CL people.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[24,27],"drawn":false},{"_id":"mIcC7M2Gs4LTzzxD","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric creates enough food and water from thin air to feed 30+CL people or produces a revitalizing heroic feast for 5 people. The food and drink of a heroic feast imparts all the benefits of a full nights sleep, restores a single point of temporary ability damage, and heals  [[/roll 1d4]]+CL points of damage.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[28,29],"drawn":false},{"_id":"2VoI0J5QO9LGHXm0","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric produces a revitalizing heroic feast for 10 people. The food and drink of a heroic feast imparts all the benefits of a full nights sleep, restores up to two points of temporary ability damage, and heals [[/roll 1d6]]+CL points of damage.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[30,31],"drawn":false},{"_id":"mMaelKspvjTcdRyr","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The earth opens up to provide a cornucopia of food and drink for the clerics faithful followers. All foodproducing locations within the clerics line of sight burst forth to provide food and water. This includes natural sources, such as fields and fruit trees that are suddenly laden with grain and food; civilized sources, such as market baskets and cooking pots, which are suddenly filled with delicious substances; and even the animals of the wild, which march forth and rest at the feet of the cleric, offering themselves for slaughter. <br /><br />This divine spectacle produces enough nourishing food to provide a solid meal for up to 100 people. Moreover, the choicest meals produce a single revitalizing heroic feast for 15 people. The food and drink of a heroic feast imparts all the benefits of a full nights sleep, restores up to three points of temporary ability damage, and heals [[/roll 1d10]]+CL points of damage.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":68,"range":[32,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"iDg58suOEIla0j7X","name":"Speak With The Dead","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.zRKbAYWXpeZMalqb"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/morbid-humour.svg","description":"<h1>Speak With The Dead</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 3</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> Self</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> Varies</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 hour</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> N/A</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 290</p><br><p>The cleric speaks with a dead creature, and it answers his questions. The cleric must be in the presence of the dead creature&rsquo;s body and be able to speak in a language that the creature understands. It will answer the cleric&rsquo;s questions to the extent of its knowledge, which is the same it possessed in life. Note that creatures with stubborn or disobedient personalities may still exhibit the same personality traits in death.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Speak With The Dead]{Speak With The Dead}</p>","results":[{"_id":"NLpeiA3WekOEvkxE","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":15,"range":[-99,15],"drawn":false},{"_id":"I0dgjSM2lh4CzLVg","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric may ask one question of a creature dead up to one week and converse for up to one round. The creatures body must be largely intact; e.g., a fragment of a shattered skull is not sufficient to answer a question, but a cadaver is.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[16,17],"drawn":false},{"_id":"IDpsKvQM5qGKyVVr","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric may ask two questions of a creature dead up to one month and converse for up to two rounds. The creatures body must be largely intact; e.g., a fragment of a shattered skull is not sufficient to answer a question, but a cadaver is.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[18,21],"drawn":false},{"_id":"MtdJlMF7iBjJ07LK","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric may ask three questions of a creature dead up to one year and converse for up to two turns. The creatures body must be largely intact; e.g., a fragment of a shattered skull is not sufficient to answer a question, but a cadaver is.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[22,23],"drawn":false},{"_id":"J5FmjyetqvQmRvE3","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric may ask four questions of a creature dead up to 10 years and converse for up to two turns. The cleric need only have a fragment of the creatures body  for example, a skull or head  but the creatures ability to communicate is limited by its remaining anatomy. If the cleric possesses only a tooth or knucklebone, for example, the deceased cannot speak, and he may need another spell to also establish a mode of communication. The cleric may communicate with the un-dead using this spell; they count as dead for purposes of the spell.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":3,"range":[24,26],"drawn":false},{"_id":"1vihRyEirokcutgP","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric may ask five questions of a creature dead up to 100 years and converse for up to two turns. The cleric need only have a fragment of the creatures body  for example, a skull or bone chip  and the creature can communicate even with only a fragmented anatomy, as its spirit speaks through it. The cleric may communicate with the un-dead using this spell, as well as other creatures whose souls have departed due to supernatural means; they count as dead for purposes of the spell.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":5,"range":[27,31],"drawn":false},{"_id":"waKRpRyJb6m52sBJ","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric may ask six questions of a creature dead up to 1,000 years and converse for up to an hour. The cleric need only have a fragment of the creatures body  for example, a skull or bone chip  and the creature can communicate even with only a fragmented anatomy, as its spirit speaks through it. The cleric may communicate with the un-dead using this spell, as well as other creatures whose souls have departed due to supernatural means; they count as dead for purposes of the spell.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[32,33],"drawn":false},{"_id":"hTvaXpUWt6jyCaZO","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric may ask any number of questions of a creature dead up to 10,000 years and converse for up to an hour. The cleric need only have a fragment of the creatures body  for example, a skull or bone chip  and the creature can communicate even with only a fragmented anatomy, as its spirit speaks through it. The cleric may communicate with the un-dead using this spell, as well as other creatures whose souls have departed due to supernatural means; they count as dead for purposes of the spell.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[34,35],"drawn":false},{"_id":"edeE1jDqZGhrUG7I","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric may ask any number of questions of a creature dead up to 100,000 years and converse for up to a day. He can communicate mentally directly with the creature and need not have any physical specimen of its corpse, though the cleric does need specific knowledge of its identity and location of birth, death, or deeds.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":64,"range":[36,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"jSBP3w65J8mjGRWp","name":"Binding","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"RollTable.9NsHtBRLNhAkAoYA"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/crossed-chains.svg","description":"<h1>Binding</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 2</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> 30 or more</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> Varies</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 round</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> Will vs. spell check DC</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 270</p><br><p>With this spell, the cleric binds a supernatural creature and forces it to obey his will. The spell is easiest if the creature has already been summoned for control via another spell. But the cleric may also cast this spell to control creatures encountered on their native planes.</p>\n<p>The cleric may target one creature already under the control of another spellcaster and summoned via another spell (for example, animal summoning, monster summoning, or invisible companion) or native to a non-material plane (for example, demons, devils, elementals, spirits, ghosts, etc.). The cleric binds that creature to obey his will instead of the will of its current master. A Will save is allowed to resist, but the Will save is made by the other spellcaster not the target creature, which is already dominated. If the check is successful, control of the bound creature transfers to the cleric casting binding. The cleric retains control for a time, after which control reverts back to the original caster (by which time the original summoning or controlling spell may have ended). This spell does not affect familiars or other creatures that voluntarily obey a spellcaster, only those under forcible control.</p>\n<p>Under certain circumstances, as noted below, the cleric may affect other targets as well.</p>\n<p>A creature under the cleric&rsquo;s control can be commanded to take any action normally within its power, similar to the animal summoning spell. The creature must be capable of hearing the cleric&rsquo;s commands and will execute them to the best of its ability. Suicidal or inherently contradictory commands grant the target another Will save to resist.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Binding]{Binding}</p>","results":[{"_id":"rnzNM6eTWaQIDMkX","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":13,"range":[-99,13],"drawn":false},{"_id":"DME0bDWeBNf9tZQJ","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric may target a creature up to 2 HD. If the spell succeeds, the cleric controls that creature for [[/roll 1d6]] rounds.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[14,15],"drawn":false},{"_id":"pXK6v2QuZ5gdU4XD","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric may target a creature up to 4 HD. If the spell succeeds, the cleric controls that creature for [[/roll 1d6]]+CL rounds.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[16,19],"drawn":false},{"_id":"FF8oCz3cW7gFCM1H","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric may target a creature up to 6 HD. If the spell succeeds, the cleric controls that creature for [[/roll 2d6]]+CL rounds.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[20,21],"drawn":false},{"_id":"hGRvtqlZ6cwSsDjZ","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric may target a creature up to 6 HD. If the spell succeeds, the cleric controls that creature for [[/roll 2d6]]+CL rounds. Alternately, the cleric may also choose to target one free-willed extraplanar creature of 4 HD or less currently on a non-native plane. <br /><br />It receives a Will save using its own modifier. The cleric controls the creature as if it were under the effects of an animal summoning spell of the same spell check. At the end of the duration, the creature reverts to its own free will.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[22,25],"drawn":false},{"_id":"CmrEY6w90q6zeDLU","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric may target a creature up to 8 HD. If the spell succeeds, the cleric controls that creature for [[/roll 2d6]]+CL turns. Alternately, the cleric may also choose to target one free-willed extraplanar creature of 6 HD or less currently on a non-native plane. <br /><br />It receives a Will save using its own modifier. The cleric controls the creature as if it were under the effects of an animal summoning spell of the same spell check. At the end of the duration, the creature reverts to its own free will.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[26,29],"drawn":false},{"_id":"oGudBZOInx9FIYwo","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric may target a creature up to 8 HD. If the spell succeeds, the cleric controls that creature for [[/roll 2d6]]+CL turns. Alternately, the cleric may also choose to target one other creature of 8 HD or less, which can be any free-willed extraplanar creature currently on a non-native plane, any mundane animal, or any unintelligent monster. <br /><br />It receives a Will save using its own modifier. The cleric controls the creature as if it were under the effects of an animal summoning spell of the same spell check. At the end of the duration, the creature reverts to its own free will.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[30,31],"drawn":false},{"_id":"uyIRnyFFuiomkbXE","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric may target a creature up to 12 HD. If the spell succeeds, the cleric controls that creature for [[/roll 2d6]]+CL hours. Alternately, the cleric may also choose any other target, whether intelligent or not,  or extraplanar or not, of up to 10 HD or less. <br /><br />It receives a Will save using its own modifier. The cleric controls the creature as if it were under the effects of an animal summoning spell of the same spell check. At the end of the duration, the creature reverts to its own free will.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[32,33],"drawn":false},{"_id":"cFa3M3iAbJ8w0b7V","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric may target any creature of any Hit Dice or power level and attempt to control that creature for [[/roll 2d6]]+CL days. At the end of the duration, the creature reverts to its own free will.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[34,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"kDtiKEj4SKrUIx01","name":"Whirling Doom","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.TN8iPJPepaNPL5W2"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/circular-sawblade.svg","description":"<h1>Whirling Doom</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 5</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> 50 per CL</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> 1 round per level</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 action</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> See below</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 303</p><br><p>The cleric creates a motionless barrier of whirling blades to bar passage and eviscerate those who come into contact with it. Enemies can attempt to fire missiles through the curtain of steel, but all creatures on the opposite side of the barrier enjoy a +4 bonus to their AC and a +2 bonus to Ref saves made against attacks originating on the other side.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Whirling Doom]{Whirling Doom}</p>","results":[{"_id":"BJPBCcFbR305jHle","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":19,"range":[-99,19],"drawn":false},{"_id":"xhjk6Zh9OqOH72e2","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The curtain occupies a vertical wall 20 square. Those passing through the blades suffer [[/roll 1d6]] points of damage per CL. If the barrier is created in an area already occupied by living creatures, they receive a Ref save to leap out of the area of effect before the blades commence slashing. A successful save indicates half damage is taken.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[20,21],"drawn":false},{"_id":"0OounkPqusY9W9qg","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The curtain occupies a vertical wall 40 square. Those passing through the blades suffer [[/roll 1d8]] points of damage per CL. If the barrier is created in an area already occupied by living creatures, they receive a Ref save to leap out of the area of effect before the blades commence slashing. A successful save indicates half damage is taken.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[22,25],"drawn":false},{"_id":"VfaWnxfOeDnS6WOL","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The curtain occupies a vertical wall 60 square or a ring-shaped wall 20 in diameter. Those passing through the blades suffer [[/roll 1d10]] points of damage per CL. If the barrier is created in an area already occupied by living creatures, they receive a Ref save to leap out of the area of effect before the blades commence slashing. A successful save indicates half damage is taken.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[26,27],"drawn":false},{"_id":"omthE3lHvT4hY2oD","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The curtain occupies a vertical wall 80 square or a ring-shaped wall 30 in diameter. Those passing through the blades suffer [[/roll 1d12]] points of damage per CL. If the barrier is created in an area already occupied by living creatures, they receive a Ref save to leap out of the area of effect before the blades commence slashing. A successful save indicates half damage is taken.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[28,29],"drawn":false},{"_id":"248JSs9KtfvNTfgM","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric creates two separate barriers. Each is either a wall 40 square or a ring-shaped wall 20 in diameter. Those passing through the blades suffer [[/roll 1d12]] points of damage per CL. If the barrier is created in an area already occupied by living creatures, they receive a Ref save to leap out of the area of effect before the blades commence slashing. A successful save indicates half damage is taken.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":6,"range":[30,35],"drawn":false},{"_id":"jmW1lzJisA2KFl2J","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric creates two separate barriers. Each is either a wall 60 square or a ring-shaped wall 30 in diameter. Those passing through the blades suffer [[/roll 1d20]] points of damage per CL. If the barrier is created in an area already occupied by living creatures, they automatically take damage with no save. Alternately, the cleric can create a barrier 10 square that moves at a rate of 20 per round in any direction of his choosing. Those caught in the barriers path must make a Ref save of suffer [[/roll 1d20]] points of damage per CL. <br /><br />Those who make their save are unharmed. Moving the barrier requires complete concentration on the part of the cleric, but he can choose to perform other actions in a round if he leaves the whirling curtain of steel motionless for that time. He may then move the barrier on subsequent rounds until the spells duration ends.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[36,37],"drawn":false},{"_id":"bRYTN1NQZV9QzEAR","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The cleric creates a terrifying field of whirling death. This barrier fills an area equal to 20 square per CL and the blades can be angled to face any direction of the clerics choosing (horizontal, vertical, angled, etc.). Those caught in the barriers path must make a Ref save of suffer [[/roll 2d20]] points of damage per CL. No save is allowed. The barrier cannot be moved, but it takes up any and all available space within the area of effect, altering its shape to fit down long hallways, oddly shaped rooms, etc.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":62,"range":[38,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"ksCDDvBmw7sS2WzN","name":"Affliction of the Gods","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.Nclzu0SNIBwdpjDo"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/heptagram.svg","description":"<h1>Affliction of the Gods</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 4</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> 50 + 10 per CL</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> Varies</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 action</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> Fort vs. spell check DC</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 295</p><br><p>The cleric strikes down his enemies with afflictions, conditions, and wounds. Those who are opposed to the cleric&rsquo;s faith (considered unholy or of opposite alignment) suffer a -2 penalty to their Fort save. All others make their saving throws as normal. The spell affects all enemies in an area 10&rsquo; square per CL. Allied creatures within the targeted area are not affected.</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Affliction of the Gods]{Affliction of the Gods}</p>","results":[{"_id":"RVwBZKz6y20IARJY","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":17,"range":[-99,17],"drawn":false},{"_id":"4X14kZ8RvbXkauWf","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"All enemies within the area of effect must make a Fort save or be deafened. Deaf creatures suffer a -4 penalty to initiative rolls and to avoid being surprised. Deaf spellcasters suffer a -2 penalty to all spell checks made while deaf. The affliction lasts for CL hours.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[18,19],"drawn":false},{"_id":"R9NdViCFeQdiO6Qb","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"All targets with the area of effect must make a Fort save or be crippled. Crippled individuals have their movement rate reduced to 5 and suffer a -2 penalty to all attack and damage rolls, saving throws, and spell checks until the condition is removed. The affliction lasts for CL hours.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[20,23],"drawn":false},{"_id":"HuNeUzsrDRq4CKPA","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"All targets with the area of effect must make a Fort save or be blinded. Blind creatures suffer a -4 penalty to initiative rolls, attack and damage rolls, saving throws, and spell checks, and are easy to surprise. In addition, a blind character firing a missile weapon is at -8 to hit and any missed shot has a 50% chance of striking a randomly determined ally. The affliction lasts for CL hours.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[24,25],"drawn":false},{"_id":"zfyOllwaTjDL3Lic","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"All targets within the area of effect must make a Fort save or temporarily lose [[/roll 1d8]] points of Strength per CL. The lost Strength returns at the normal rate once the spell has ended. Creatures whose Strength is reduced to zero fall unconscious until theyve regained one or more Strength points. This weakness lasts for a full 24 hours.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[26,27],"drawn":false},{"_id":"mVFqxJRqFnzdzwAn","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"All targets within the area of effect are afflicted with a hideous, flesh-eating bacteria. Each round, the affected must make a Fort save or take [[/roll 1d6]] points of compounded damage every round for CL rounds; i.e., [[/roll 1d6]] on the first round, [[/roll 2d6]] on the second round, [[/roll 3d6]] on the third round, and so on. <br /><br />Success on a Fort save avoids damage only on the current round; it does not stop the spells effect on future rounds. The bacteria devour all organic materials worn or carried by the victims, destroying leather, cloth, wood, and similar materials in [[/roll 1d4]] rounds. A neutralize disease spell destroys the bacteria as does magical flame (fireball, control fire, etc.), but the target takes full damage from the fire.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":6,"range":[28,33],"drawn":false},{"_id":"bz4x1k9WFS7TDaJO","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"All target within the area of effect must make a Fort save or be stricken with a plague of divine origin. The disease immediately causes  [[/roll 1d10]]+CL damage to the targets and the loss of a point of Luck. The disease continues to ravage the targets bodies after the spell ends and can easily prove fatal. <br /><br />Each subsequent day the target is diseased, it must make a DC 25 Fort save. Failure to do so means they remain ill and suffer the loss of another Luck point and an additional [[/roll 1d6]] damage. Each day after the first, the DC of the Fort save is reduced by 1 until the target makes his save, the disease runs its course, or the disease kills its subject. The disease last for 4 days plus 1 day per CL.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[34,35],"drawn":false},{"_id":"oCYgRjZlX4gQOTwq","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"All targets with the area of effect must make a Fort save or spontaneously combust! They and all nonmagical possessions burst into flames that do [[/roll 1d10]] points of damage each round they remain on fire. Extinguishing the magical flame requires a full rounds action and the victim must make a DC 20 Ref check to put out the fire. The fires continue until extinguished or the victim dies.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[36,37],"drawn":false},{"_id":"UzxOcDOpN8Na3K2h","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The gaze of the clerics deity turns upon the heathens within the area of effect and completely decimates all who fail their Fort save. The targets melt into pools of bloody slime and runny flesh that quickly evaporates as if they had never been. <br /><br />Due to the deitys personal involvement in this effect, all spell checks by the cleric suffer a -10 penalty for a full week afterwards. His deity has helped him enough and is likely to ignore any further requests until a weeks time has passed. This modifier can be removed at the judges discretion if the cleric undertakes a great task in his deitys name.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":62,"range":[38,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"mWCayJ8rx5c3Urki","name":"Blessing Ally","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.PdUhHE8DgUqqHncI"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/holy-water.svg","description":"<h1>Blessing Ally</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 1</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> Self or touch</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> 1 turn or more</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 action or more (see below)</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> N/A</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 255</p><br><p>The cleric beseeches the blessing of his god. If bestowed, this blessing can be a great boon to the success of his endeavors. The spell can be cast on the cleric himself, on an object, or on one of the cleric&rsquo;s allies.</p>\n<p>The spell is most effective on allies with the same alignment. Casting this spell on a target with a different alignment incurs a -1 penalty to the spell check, and casting the spell on a target with an opposite alignment or in allegiance to an opposed deity incurs a -2 penalty.</p>\n<p>The casting time reflects prayer and meditation as the cleric uses his holy symbol to conduct the blessing ritual. Blessings cast under auspicious circumstances receive a bonus of +1 to +4, according to the judge&rsquo;s discretion. Such circumstances include casting in the temple of the cleric&rsquo;s god, casting on a sacred holiday, or casting with the use of a holy relic. Likewise, casting under inauspicious circumstances, such as in an unholy enemy temple, receives a penalty ranging from -1 to -4.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Blessing Ally]{Blessing Ally}</p>","results":[{"_id":"g6ZFzl7gCpRO2CC4","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":11,"range":[-99,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"JdWvjOUOPaLHkRke","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The ally receives a +1 bonus to all attack rolls for 1 round.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[12,13],"drawn":false},{"_id":"MrMOFdVhm3Vu9dQ5","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The ally receives a +1 bonus to all attack rolls for 1 turn.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[14,17],"drawn":false},{"_id":"8LlCUkbkD8upTMfm","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The ally receives a +1 bonus to all attack rolls, damage rolls, saving throws, and skill checks, and spell checks for 1 turn.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[18,19],"drawn":false},{"_id":"alMuqA76stgfXwWJ","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The ally receives a +2 bonus to all attack rolls, damage rolls, saving throws, skill checks, and spell checks for 1 turn.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[20,23],"drawn":false},{"_id":"O4jsK4IRVqF2qYCx","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The ally receives a bonus to all attack rolls, damage rolls, saving throws, skill checks, and spell checks. The bonus is equal to  [[/roll 1d3]]+CL (rolled at time of casting) and lasts for 1 turn.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":4,"range":[24,27],"drawn":false},{"_id":"c1jnezvqNhPNjMrQ","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The ally receives a bonus to all attack rolls, damage rolls, saving throws, skill checks, and spell checks. The bonus is equal to  [[/roll 1d3]]+CL (rolled at time of casting) and lasts for 1 turn. In addition, the ally radiates a holy aura. Allies within 5 of the ally receive the same blessing as long as they remain within the aura.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[28,29],"drawn":false},{"_id":"akG8lpdhZkpiiEZ7","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The ally receives a bonus to all attack rolls, damage rolls, saving throws, skill checks, and spell checks. The bonus is equal to  [[/roll 1d3]]+CL (rolled at time of casting) and lasts for 1 turn. In addition, the ally radiates a holy aura. Allies within 10 of the ally receive the same blessing as long as they remain within the aura.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":2,"range":[30,31],"drawn":false},{"_id":"tPctvpKEut0UPeRT","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The ally receives a bonus to all attack rolls, damage rolls, saving throws, skill checks, and spell checks. The bonus is equal to  [[/roll 1d3]]+CL (rolled at time of casting) and lasts for 1 turn. In addition, the ally radiates a holy aura. Allies within 20 of the ally receive the same blessing as long as they remain within the aura.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":68,"range":[32,99],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"n4jOcPWCP7DPHoWU","name":"Word of Command","permission":{"default":0,"U5X07uKi3FMVWkQ1":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendium.spell-tables.DFfFom3pla3ECR7r"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/lightning-shout.svg","description":"<h1>Word of Command</h1><p><strong>Level:</strong> 1</p><p><strong>Range:</strong> 30 or more</p><p><strong>Duration:</strong> 1 round or more</p><p><strong>Casting Time:</strong> 1 round</p><p><strong>Save:</strong> Will save vs. spell check</p><p><strong>Page:</strong> 268</p><br><p>The cleric speaks a powerful word that carries with it the commanding will of his deity. Creatures hearing the word are bound to obey. The word must be a single word, which must describe an action. For example, &ldquo;go,&rdquo; &ldquo;attack,&rdquo; &ldquo;retreat,&rdquo; &ldquo;speak,&rdquo; &ldquo;swim,&rdquo; &ldquo;grovel,&rdquo; &ldquo;silence,&rdquo; and so on. The word must be spoken in the direction of a single sentient target within range. That target receives a Will save to resist; if failed, it must obey the command for its next round. The command is interpreted by the creature&rsquo;s natural thought processes; e.g., issuing an &ldquo;attack&rdquo; command to an herbivore may have a different response than to a carnivore. The word of command cannot be longer in length than a single word and may be subject to misinterpretation. If the command is completely contrary to a creature&rsquo;s natural instinct, it receives a +4 bonus to its Will save to resist; for example, commanding a desert lizard to &ldquo;swim&rdquo; or any command of &ldquo;suicide.&rdquo;</p><br><p><strong>Spell Data:</strong> @Compendium[dcc-core-book.dcc-core-spell-journals.Word of Command]{Word of Command}</p>","results":[{"_id":"VA1tbFCnuarAnGg4","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Failure.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":11,"range":[-99,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"ZIKtpVrqOzVZDdr7","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The c